main event: Sighting of 9 unidentified blue objects of varying size and brightness, flying together in a random pattern at medium to high altitudes, with a light red halo in the area.
interesting points: The objects were observed by the USS President Vanburen at coordinates 38.30N 74.20W.
The weather was cloudy with wind and sea motion.

The analysis sheet describes a separate sighting of 3 bright green objects moving rapidly with a flickering motion, about 1/4 the diameter of conventional aircraft, with bright orange sparks visible on 2 of the objects.
The green objects seemed to climb and fall in their flight, and the weather was clear and cold.
The source reliability is evaluated as 'probably good'.
sighted object: 9 blue objects and 3 bright green objects
